# ============================================================
# .cursorrules — Spec App Project
# ============================================================
# This file is read by Cursor before every prompt.
# Do not remove or rename this file.
# ============================================================

## Project Overview
Specification Clarification Application.
Workflow-based AI system that converts Minutes of Meeting (MOM)
into structured specification documents with ambiguity/risk detection.
Not a chat AI. AI is only called in controlled workflow steps.
2 developers. Pre-production / university project + talent competition.

## Tech Stack
- Backend:     NestJS (TypeScript)
- Database:    PostgreSQL 16, TypeORM
- Queue:       AWS SQS (async AI generation)
- AI:          OpenAI API direct (gpt-4o-mini)
- Storage:     AWS S3 (private bucket)
- Secrets:     AWS Secrets Manager (injected by ECS at runtime)
- Frontend:    Vercel (Next.js) — separate repo
- Mobile:      Review-only app — separate repo
- CI/CD:       GitHub Actions → ECR → ECS Fargate

## Project Structure
backend/
  src/
    main.ts                          → HTTP API entry point
    worker.main.ts                   → SQS worker entry point (no HTTP)
    app.module.ts                    → root module
    constant/
      sql-column.constant.ts         → column type constants
    entities/
      base.entity.ts                 → base entity (id + audit columns)
      *.entity.ts                    → one file per entity
    modules/
      user/
      template/
      spec/
      lookup/
      queue/                         → SQS producer (used by API)
      worker/                        → SQS consumer (used by worker)

## Entities
All entities extend BaseEntity from backend/src/entities/base.entity.ts
BaseEntity contains:
- id: UUID primary key, generated with uuid_generate_v4()
- createdBy: UUID FK → user.id, nullable
- createdOn: timestamptz, default NOW()
- updatedBy: UUID FK → user.id, nullable
- updatedOn: timestamptz, default NOW()
- deletedBy: UUID FK → user.id, nullable
- deletedOn: timestamptz, nullable

Never repeat audit columns on individual entities.
Never add id column on individual entities.
Always import column types from backend/src/constant/sql-column.constant.ts.
No magic strings for column types anywhere.

Entity files: backend/src/entities/
- base.entity.ts
- user.entity.ts
- language.entity.ts
- spec-status.entity.ts
- section-type.entity.ts
- risk-type.entity.ts
- main-template.entity.ts
- template.entity.ts
- template-section.entity.ts
- main-generated-spec.entity.ts
- generated-spec.entity.ts
- generated-spec-section.entity.ts
- spec-risk.entity.ts

## TypeORM Rules
- synchronize: false always, no exceptions
- No eager: true on any relation
- Always use @JoinColumn({ name: 'snake_case_column' }) on @ManyToOne side
- camelCase property names, TypeORM maps to snake_case DB columns automatically
- nullable FK columns use { nullable: true } in both @Column and @ManyToOne
- Relations loaded explicitly via relations: {} in queries, never auto-loaded
- All relations define both sides: @ManyToOne on child, @OneToMany on parent
- No @Exclude() decorators on entities

## NestJS Config Pattern
- ConfigModule.forRoot() in AppModule only — loads .env locally, no-op on ECS
- ConfigModule.forFeature(registerAs('domain', () => ({...}))) per domain module
- Each domain has its own ConfigService wrapper class
- No USE_AWS_SECRET flag
- No AWS SDK calls at bootstrap
- All config reads from process.env — source does not matter to the app
- ECS injects Secrets Manager values into process.env before container starts

Planned registerAs domains:
- 'database'  → DB_HOST, DB_PORT, DB_USER, DB_PASS, DB_NAME
- 'openai'    → OPENAI_API_KEY
- 's3'        → S3_BUCKET, S3_REGION
- 'sqs'       → SQS_QUEUE_URL, SQS_REGION

## Service / Controller Pattern
- Never return raw TypeORM entities from controllers
- Always map entity to DTO before returning from service
- Use static DTO.from(entity) factory pattern for mapping
- TypeORM relations loaded explicitly only when needed
- No @Exclude() needed — DTO mapping handles response shaping

## Async Generation Flow (SQS)
API layer responsibilities:
1. Validate request
2. Save GeneratedSpec to DB with status PROCESSING
3. Save MOM content to S3
4. Push job to SQS queue
5. Return job accepted response immediately to user

Worker layer responsibilities:
1. Consume job from SQS
2. Call OpenAI API (gpt-4o-mini, one call per generation)
3. Save GeneratedSpecSections to DB
4. Save SpecRisks to DB
5. Update GeneratedSpec status → COMPLETED
6. Update MainGeneratedSpec.currentVersion pointer

On failure:
- Set GeneratedSpec status → FAILED
- Do NOT update currentVersion pointer
- currentVersion keeps pointing to last stable COMPLETED version

## Architecture Rules
- Never call OpenAI from API layer (HTTP request lifecycle)
- Never call OpenAI from a controller or service triggered by HTTP
- OpenAI is only called from the SQS worker process
- Never update currentVersion before COMPLETED status
- Never update currentVersion on FAILED status
- API returns immediately after pushing to SQS — never waits for AI

## Soft Delete Rules
- Never hard delete any record
- Soft delete only via deletedOn + deletedBy on all tables
- When querying active records always filter: WHERE deleted_on IS NULL
- TypeORM @SoftDelete() or manual deletedOn filter — be consistent

## Database Schema Decisions
- MainGeneratedSpec.currentVersion is a denormalized pointer to the
  latest COMPLETED GeneratedSpec version
  Reason: avoids JOIN + status filter to find latest version on every read
- Language is locked per GeneratedSpec version (not changeable after generation)
- Spec content is read-only after generation (no UPDATE on spec content)
- Regenerate always creates a new GeneratedSpec version, never mutates existing
- Template change creates a new MainGeneratedSpec root, not a new version
- MOM stored in S3, store s3Key + s3Bucket (never full URLs)
- AI metadata stored per GeneratedSpec version:
  aiModel, promptTokens, completionTokens, totalTokens, generationTimeMs

## Indexes (already in schema.sql, do not re-create)
- user(email)
- user(username)
- main_template(user_id, deleted_on)
- template(main_template_id, version)
- template_section(template_id, sort_order)
- main_generated_spec(user_id, deleted_on)
- generated_spec(main_spec_id, version)
- generated_spec(status_id)
- generated_spec_section(spec_id, sort_order)
- spec_risk(spec_id)
- spec_risk(section_id)

## Local Dev Stack
- spec-app-pg:         PostgreSQL 16 (localhost:5432)
- spec-app-redis:      Redis 7 (localhost:6379) — reserved, not wired yet
- spec-app-sonarqube:  SonarQube community (localhost:9000)
- SQS: real AWS dev queue (no localstack)
  Queue name: spec-app-dev-generation-queue

## ECS Deployment
Single Docker image, two ECS task definitions:
- spec-app-api-task    → CMD: node dist/main.js
- spec-app-worker-task → CMD: node dist/worker.main.js

GitHub Actions builds once, pushes one image to ECR.
Both tasks pull same image, different CMD override per task definition.

## AWS Infrastructure
- VPC: 2 public subnets + 2 private subnets
- No NAT Gateway (cost saving)
- No ALB (cost saving, pre-prod)
- ECS Fargate in public subnet
- RDS PostgreSQL in private subnet (no public access)
- S3 private bucket
- SQS queue for generation jobs
- Secrets Manager for all secrets

## What NOT To Do
- Do NOT use synchronize: true
- Do NOT use eager loading on any relation
- Do NOT return raw entities from controllers
- Do NOT call AWS SDK for secrets at bootstrap
- Do NOT add @Exclude() decorators
- Do NOT hard delete any record
- Do NOT update currentVersion on FAILED status
- Do NOT call OpenAI from HTTP request lifecycle
- Do NOT use BullMQ (using SQS directly)
- Do NOT use localstack (use real AWS dev SQS queue)
- Do NOT add NAT Gateway or ALB to infra
- Do NOT use Aurora Serverless (not in current scope)
- Do NOT store full S3 URLs (store key + bucket only)
- Do NOT add chat AI interface (system is workflow-based only)
- Do NOT repeat audit columns on individual entities (use BaseEntity)
- Do NOT add id column on individual entities (use BaseEntity)
